query.prompt:
Please translate each line literally into English and Cornish.

112 Quel che par sì membruto e che s’accorda,
113 cantando, con colui dal maschio naso,
114 d’ogne valor portò cinta la corda;

115 e se re dopo lui fosse rimaso
116 lo giovanetto che retro a lui siede,
117 ben andava il valor di vaso in vaso,

118 che non si puote dir de l’altre rede;
119 Iacomo e Federigo hanno i reami;
120 del retaggio miglior nessun possiede.

query.result:
**English:**

112 He who seems so strong and who sings in harmony
113 with the one with the manly nose,
114 wore the cord of every virtue;

115 and if the young man who sits behind him
116 had remained king after him,
117 then virtue would have passed from vessel to vessel,

118 which cannot be said of the other heirs;
119 James and Frederick have the kingdoms;
120 no one possesses the better inheritance.

**Cornish:**

112 An hini a-wra mar membrus ha a-wra y kevri,
113 ow tos orth ha’n hini a-wra an tron mar maskla,
114 a-wra an gord a bub oll an virtudes a-wra y wonn;

115 ha pan vynnas an yowynk a-wra y’n kevri
116 dhe vos re wosa henna,
117 ena a-vedhas an virtudes a-dhia les dhe les,

118 an peth nyns gallos leverel a’n aral erel;
119 Iacomo ha Federigo a-wra an rewlysow;
120 neb aral nyns a-wra an ertach gwella.
